; 1) What is the total calculated by adding the 10 numbers? x7FFF
; 2) Describe how R2 is used by the program. (What does it represent?)
;    R2 represents the addresses of the 10 numbers
; 3) Why is R2 incremented in the instruction at x3005? 
;    R2 increments to get the address of the next of the 10 numbers.
; 4) Why is the value 10 loaded into R4? 
;    R4 acts at counter to tell the program when to stop

; R0 - counter
; R1 - data at x3100
; R2 - mask
; R3 - R7 - nothing



0011 0000 0000 0000         ; Set PC at x3000
0101 000 000 1 00000        ; Clear R0
0010 001 011 1 11110        ; get data from address x3100 and put in R1
0001 010 000  1 00001       ; mask set in R2
0101 110  001 000 010       ; AND R1 and R2
0000 010 000000001          ; Branch if equal to 0
0001 000 000 1 00001        ; add 1 to R0 if there is a 1
0001 010 010 000 010        ; shift mask to left R2
0000 101 111111011          ; if mask is not 0 go back to 3003
0011 000  011 1 11000       ; store in x3101
1111 0000 00100101          ; halt


